How to create multiple angular projects using single nodu modules library..
1:>Create a new folder ex: Angular_POC
2:>open cmd prompt with that directory: C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC
3:>C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC>ng new MyApps --create-application false
4:>cd MyApps
5:>C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC\MyApps>ng g application my-first-app
6:>Open the project in VS code.
7:> ng serve my-first-app (http://localhost:4200/) 
8:> PS C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC\MyApps> ng g c components/comp1 --project="my-first-app"
8.1:> PS C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC\MyApps> ng g s services/myservice --project="my-first-app" 
9:> in order to create one more angular application in the same folder which contains node_modules library
10:> PS C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC\MyApps> ng g application my-second-app
11:> ng serve my-second-app (http://localhost:54228/)
12:> PS C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC\MyApps> ng g c components/comp1 --project="my-second-app"
12.1:>PS C:\Drive_D\Angular_POC\MyApps> ng g s services/myservice --project="my-second-app"
